**Project Overview**  
Airlienda is a comprehensive ERP system designed to manage hostel operations efficiently. The goal of this project is to protect hostel resources, facilitate bookings, track occupancy, handle notifications, report faults, and manage various administrative activities within a hostel.  
**Features**  
	•	**User Authentication & Registration**: Secure user registration and login with password validation.  
	•	**Room Management**: Create, update, delete, and view available rooms and their occupancy status.  
	•	**Booking System**: Users can book rooms based on availability, and the system updates room occupancy accordingly.  
	•	**Notification System**: Send and receive notifications for bookings, payments, and fault resolutions.  
	•	**Fault Reporting**: Allow users to report faults related to their rooms and inventory items.  
	•	**Admin Dashboard**: Hostel admins have access to a dashboard for managing bookings, users, notifications, and fault reports.  
	•	**Automated System Updates**: Regular system backups, monitoring, and health checks to ensure smooth operations.  
**Tech Stack**  
**Backend**  
	•	**Python (Django Framework)**: Backend logic, models, and views.  
	•	**Django Rest Framework (DRF)**: API endpoints for handling client-server communication.  
**Frontend**  
	•	**HTML/CSS/Bootstrap**: UI and styling for user and admin dashboards.  
	•	**JavaScript (jQuery & AJAX)**: Interactive client-side components.  
**Database**  
	•	**PostgreSQL**: Robust database for handling relational data, supporting scalability and data integrity.  
**Server**  
	•	**Gunicorn & Nginx**: Gunicorn as WSGI server for serving Django, proxied by Nginx for efficient request handling.  
	•	**AWS EC2**: Deployment of the system on an AWS EC2 instance.  
**Installation and Setup**  
	1\.	**Clone the Repository**:  
git clone https://github.com/username/airlienda.git  
cd airlienda  
2\.	**Create a Virtual Environment**:  
python3 \-m venv airlienda\_env  
source airlienda\_env/bin/activate  
3\.	**Install Dependencies**:  
pip install \-r requirements.txt  
4\.	**Database Setup**:  
	•	Create a .env file in the root folder and configure your database credentials.  
	•	Run migrations to set up the database schema:  
python manage.py migrate

5\.	**Run Server Locally**:  
python manage.py runserver

**Usage**  
	•	**Admin Dashboard**: Navigate to /admin to manage users, rooms, bookings, notifications, and fault reports.  
	•	**User Portal**: Users can register, log in, book rooms, view bookings, and report faults through the main interface.
